==English==
===Etymology===
from ''hyper-'' above, extra  +  ''-(o)nym'' name.  in Gk.: υπερνύμιον, literally meaning 'extra name'.

===Noun===
'''hypernym'''

#{{linguistics}} a superordinate grouping A which includes subordinate grouping(s) B; for example, ''musical instrument'' is a hypernym of ''guitar'', because ''musical instrument'' includes ''guitar''

